org.apache.flink.runtime.state.heap

类 NestedMapsStateTable<K,N,S>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flink.runtime.state.heap.StateTable<K,N,S>
      • org.apache.flink.runtime.state.heap.NestedMapsStateTable<K,N,S>
  • 类型参数:
    K - type of key.
    N - type of namespace.
    S - type of state.

    @Internal
public class NestedMapsStateTable<K,N,S>
extends StateTable<K,N,S>
    This implementation of StateTable uses nested HashMap objects. It is also maintaining a partitioning by key-group.

    In contrast to CopyOnWriteStateTable, this implementation does not support asynchronous snapshots. However, it might have a better memory footprint for some use-cases, e.g. it is naturally de-duplicating namespace objects.

    • 字段详细资料

      • state

        private final java.util.Map<N,java.util.Map<K,S>>[] state
        Map for holding the actual state objects. The outer array represents the key-groups. The nested maps provide an outer scope by namespace and an inner scope by key.

      • keyGroupOffset

        private final int keyGroupOffset
        The offset to the contiguous key groups

      • transform

        public <T> void transform(N namespace,
                          T value,
                          StateTransformationFunction<S,T> transformation)
                   throws java.lang.Exception
        从类复制的说明: StateTable
        Applies the given StateTransformationFunction to the state (1st input argument), using the given value as second input argument. The result of StateTransformationFunction.apply(Object, Object) is then stored as the new state. This function is basically an optimization for get-update-put pattern.
        指定者:
        transform 在类中 StateTable<K,N,S>
        参数:
        namespace - the namespace. Not null.
        value - the value to use in transforming the state. Can be null.
        transformation - the transformation function.
        抛出:
        java.lang.Exception - if some exception happens in the transformation function.
